## Cohort Discovery — Stage 1 (deterministic engine, UI, persistence, materialisation)

Context: New Digital-Twin feature for business-friendly cohort
discovery — group entities that travel together using rule-based
linkage (shared resources via predicates) and compatibility constraints
(same-value, value-equals, value-in, value-range). The feature is
purely additive: the existing reasoning engines (OWL 2 RL, SWRL, SPARQL
CONSTRUCT, Decision Tables, Aggregate Rules) are untouched. Cohort
rules live in their own slot (`ontology.cohort_rules`) and are
versioned through the existing registry (Volume + Lakebase). Stage 2
(NL agent → CohortRule JSON) reuses every Stage 1 endpoint as its
toolbox — no parallel pipeline.

Design spec: `releasereq/cohort_design.md` (canonical).
User docs: `docs/cohort_discovery.md` (4 worked examples).

