## Cohort Discovery — Stage 2 (natural-language rule-generation agent)

Context: Stage 2 of the Cohort Discovery feature. A dedicated agent
(`agents/agent_cohort/`) translates free-text prompts like *"find
consultants who can be staffed together — exempts only with exempts"*
into a validated `CohortRule` JSON. The agent reuses every Stage 1
endpoint as its toolbox (no parallel pipeline) and never writes — the
user reviews and saves the proposed rule in the existing form. UI
adds a single-line prompt input above the cohorts page with a
collapsible agent trace (tool calls, durations, iterations, tokens).

Design spec: `releasereq/cohort_design.md` §12.
User docs: `docs/cohort_discovery.md` §9.

Changes:

1. src/agents/agent_cohort/__init__.py (new)
   - Stage 2 agent package; exports `run_agent` and `AgentResult`.

2. src/agents/agent_cohort/tools.py (new)
   - Six tools wired to existing Stage 1 endpoints:
     `list_classes` (compact ontology summary), `list_properties_of`
     (data + object properties for a class, filtered by domain),
     `count_class_members` (live class instance count),
     `sample_values_of` (distinct property values, limit clamped to
     30), `propose_rule` (client-side `CohortRule.validate()`; on
     success parks the canonical dict on `ToolContext.metadata`),
     `dry_run` (cluster body trimmed to top 5 sizes for prompt
     economy).
   - All read-only except `propose_rule`, which only validates.

3. src/agents/agent_cohort/engine.py (new)
   - One-shot agent loop mirroring `agent_dtwin_chat/engine.py`
     (same retry, trace decorator, OpenAI-compatible schema). Adds
     `AgentResult.proposed_rule` populated from `ctx.metadata`.
   - System prompt enforces the 7-step workflow (introspect → propose
     → optionally dry-run once → terse markdown reply) and forbids
     write-side intent. 10-iteration cap.

4. src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py
   - Added `POST /dtwin/cohorts/agent` route (right after the cohort
     UC probe routes). Body: `{prompt, history?}`. Response:
     `{success, rule, reply, tools, iterations, usage}`. Reuses
     `_chat_resolve_domain_name` and `_auto_discover_llm_endpoint`.
     Forwards session cookies + Databricks-Apps `X-Forwarded-*`
     headers so loopback tool calls authenticate as the same user.
   - No write-side dependency declared (the agent does not save
     anything; saving still goes through the BUILDER-protected
     `POST /cohorts/rules`).

5. src/front/templates/partials/dtwin/_query_cohorts.html
   - Added the *Cohort Discovery agent* banner above the form: a
     full-width prompt input + *Generate rule* button, with a
     collapsible agent trace section. Pressing Enter triggers the
     run.

6. src/front/static/query/js/query-cohorts.js
   - Added `runAgent()`, `_renderAgentTrace()`, `_applyRuleFromAgent()`.
     Hits `POST /dtwin/cohorts/agent`, hydrates the form with the
     proposed rule (as a draft — no `activeRuleId` is set), and
     renders the tool-call list with durations.

7. src/front/static/query/css/query-cohorts.css
   - Added `.cohort-agent-banner` (dashed primary border, light tint)
     and `.cohort-agent-trace` (scrollable 220px max-height list).

8. tests/test_agent_cohort_tools.py (new)
   - 19 unit tests, one block per tool. Uses `httpx.MockTransport` to
     swap out the loopback HTTP client. Covers happy path, missing
     args, backend failure, HTTP error surfaces, limit clamping, and
     the deterministic offline behaviour of `propose_rule` (parks
     valid rules on `ctx.metadata`, surfaces validation errors,
     refuses non-dict inputs).

9. tests/test_agent_cohort_engine.py (new)
   - 3 integration tests that script the LLM through
     `unittest.mock.patch` and verify: full round-trip yields
     `AgentResult.proposed_rule` matching the rule the LLM proposed;
     invalid `propose_rule` arguments leave `proposed_rule=None`;
     LLM failures are surfaced via `result.error`.

10. docs/cohort_discovery.md
    - Replaced the *Stage 2 (planned)* section with the shipped
      version: tool table, workflow, API contract, UX walkthrough,
